cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the automated analysis of web pages for security and privacy issues. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the impact of the service on end-users and privacy regulators. Additionally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as the service involves the development of software tools and the analysis of web pages in a networked environment. Finally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) could be relevant as the service aims to improve transparency and ease of use for end-users.
